Subject: Improved Eberspacher BN-4 performance

Fiddling, I find that angling the fuel pump verically and making the fuel 
line from the pump to the heater as diect and short as possible, I get 
stronger bursts of fuel into the combustion chamber resulting in a cleaner 
burn, less smoke and fumes and cooler running.

Cheers,

John
